The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Buddha to speak on Rawla case
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Buddha to speak on Rawla case
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	The chief minister will make a statement in the Assembly on Thursday on the suicide by La Martiniere for Boys student Rouvanjit Rawla, Speaker Hashim Abdul Halim has said.        
	RSP member Mohammad Refatullah raised the issue in the House on Tuesday, demanding the state governments intervention. The government cannot remain silent as the family of Rouvanjit is seeking justice. It should intervene in the matter, Refatullah said.        
	Speaker Halim then asked the government chief whip, Syed Mohammad Masih of the CPM, to take up the matter with chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee, who is also in charge of the home department. The Speaker later said in his chamber that Bhattacharjee would make a statement on the issue in the House on Thursday.        
	Calcutta polices detective department would start investigation on the fake HRD team visit to La Martiniere for Boys once officers who are in Delhi to record the statement of a senior ministry official return to the city.         
	We need to talk to the complainant in person and collect his signature. We hope to start the probe from Wednesday after the formalities have been taken care of, said detective chief Damayanti Sen.        
	Smart bail: Sanjay Smart, the La Martiniere for Boys teacher arrested for allegedly demanding bribe to promote a student, was granted bail on Tuesday.                                                                                                                                                          
